                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14233628" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Wed, 3 Dec 2014 22:51:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First diff out on Phabricator: &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.facebook.net/D29685&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.facebook.net/D29685&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14233904" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Thu, 4 Dec 2014 04:34:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Everyone seems okay with this first patch. We still need to do more work on this JIRA to completely remove 0.89-fb dependencies. This one would get us unblocked w.r.t work being done in other JIRAs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14236790" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Sat, 6 Dec 2014 14:01:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached second patch after addressing Ted&apos;s comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14236880" author="stack" created="Sat, 6 Dec 2014 16:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks like good progress.  You don&apos;t need our +1 for commit to branch. You just need blessing of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt; OR &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=amitanand&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;amitanand&quot;&gt;Amitanand Aiyer&lt;/a&gt; and for them to do the commit on the branch for you.  Please do keep going via JIRA and posting patches if you don&apos;t mind because it helps us follow-along.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d be interested in learning if any plans for unifying QuorumInfo and master branches accounting of replicas by making note in hbase:meta &amp;#8211; we can chat on this at some point but too early for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14236890" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Sat, 6 Dec 2014 17:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;! Yes, awaiting either of them to commit this patch. We would be posting patches. This JIRA might have multiple patches, since this has multiple parts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can discuss the integration of master with QuorumInfo this once we land &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12499&quot; title=&quot;Integrate the RAFT Protocol into WAL&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12499&quot;&gt;HBASE-12499&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12500&quot; title=&quot;Update the read/write path of HBase w.r.t the RAFT Protocol&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12500&quot;&gt;HBASE-12500&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14236969" author="eclark" created="Sat, 6 Dec 2014 20:56:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed 002 version of the patch to the feature branch. Everything compiled well. Tests are currently running.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14237033" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2014 03:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome! Thanks Elliott! This is a somewhat bigger &apos;task&apos; with multiple parts, but JIRA doesn&apos;t let me create subtask for this, since this is already a subtask of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12259&quot; title=&quot;Bring quorum based write ahead log into HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12259&quot;&gt;HBASE-12259&lt;/a&gt;. Do you suggest we file separate JIRAs, or just keep adding multiple patches here and we can commit with the same JIRA number?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14237045" author="eclark" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2014 04:41:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would say multiple jiras would be easier that way the commits are easy to match up to the patches that were posted last on jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14237166" author="gaurav.menghani" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2014 14:53:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, so I am going to rename this JIRA to indicate that this was only for HRegionInfo. We will file separate JIRAs for the remaining work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
